An Act touching the moneys & coyns of England. Laws, etc. England and Wales.
[2], 349-351, [i.e. 5] p.
printed for Edward Husband, printer to the Parliament of England, [London : 1649]
With an order to print dated 17 July 1649. Caption title; caption ornament; initial letter; text in black letter Imprint from colophon. Signatures: 3P² . Also issued as part of a through-paged set with a table for the entire set added. On 3P: last word of first line of text: "of"; first word of line below initial: "rity"; last word of last full line of text on first page: "in". Reproduction of the original in the British Library. Annotation in Thomason's hand on p. [1] at beginning: date July 5 1649, and title.
